24
00:00:59,469 --> 00:01:03,110
There are many, many ways China does this.

25
00:01:03,110 --> 00:01:05,590
But today I’m going to focus on one way:

26
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:06,590
Mass surveillance.

27
00:01:06,590 --> 00:01:10,130
You’ve probably heard of the Chinese telecom
company Huawei.

28
00:01:10,130 --> 00:01:14,130
It’s technically a private company...maybe...

29
00:01:14,130 --> 00:01:17,000
but it has strong connections to the Chinese
government

30
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,510
and the Chinese Communist Party.

31
00:01:18,510 --> 00:01:19,510
Huawei

32
00:01:19,510 --> 00:01:24,640
is being used to build a vast surveillance
network in African countries.

33
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:28,090
They’re even training police in how to use
their technology

34
00:01:28,090 --> 00:01:32,200
to crack down on anyone who questions that
country’s government.

35
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:35,520
A lot of African dictators simply don’t
have the resources

36
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:38,630
to build their own surveillance infrastructure
from scratch.

37
00:01:38,630 --> 00:01:41,210
So they turn to China for help.

38
00:01:41,210 --> 00:01:43,740
Through multi-million dollar deals with Huawei,

39
00:01:43,740 --> 00:01:46,540
they’re bringing China’s techno-autocracy

40
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:49,600
to one of the poorest continents on Earth.

41
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,770
Because sure, people may not have clean drinking
water,

42
00:01:52,770 --> 00:01:57,210
but at least they have Huawei security cameras
on every corner!

43
00:01:57,210 --> 00:02:01,220
The Chinese giant supplies most of the 3g
and 4G cell towers...

44
00:02:01,220 --> 00:02:04,380
and Surveillance cameras equipped with facial
recognition.

45
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:07,189
Even in this village where a lot of homes
don't even have\h electricity

46
00:02:07,189 --> 00:02:10,700
there's a brand new set of surveillance cameras
behind me.

47
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:12,950
That was from this Wall Street Journal Investigation.

48
00:02:12,950 --> 00:02:17,640
Huawei is building the backbone of future
5G networks.

49
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:21,320
But it’s also building surveillance systems
around the world.

50
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:24,420
The Wall Street Journal investigation looked
at police documents

51
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:26,780
and parliamentary committee documents.

52
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:30,130
They interviewed diplomats, cyber-defense
officials,

53
00:02:30,130 --> 00:02:33,300
and opposition activists who have been targeted,

54
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:35,700
plus more than a dozen senior security officials

55
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:38,920
working with Huawei in African countries.

56
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:42,640
They found that Huawei is actively making
countries in Africa

57
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,770
a worse place to live.

58
00:02:44,770 --> 00:02:47,530
At least if you’re not part of the ruling
elite.

59
00:02:47,530 --> 00:02:49,420
The Wall Street Journal investigation says,

60
00:02:49,420 --> 00:02:51,750
“According to senior security officials,

61
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:54,490
embedded, hands-on Huawei technicians

62
00:02:54,490 --> 00:02:57,800
train security forces and cyber-surveillance
units

63
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:00,970
that regularly snoop on political opposition.”

64
00:03:00,970 --> 00:03:03,070
For example, “In Zambia...

65
00:03:03,070 --> 00:03:05,130
Huawei technicians helped the government access

66
00:03:05,130 --> 00:03:07,740
the phones and Facebook pages of a team

67
00:03:07,740 --> 00:03:11,470
of opposition bloggers running a pro-opposition
news site.”

68
00:03:11,470 --> 00:03:16,360
Good, so Huawei is helping African dictators
silence political opponents.

69
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:19,890
Then, there’s also what Huawei calls Safe
Cities,

70
00:03:19,890 --> 00:03:23,270
or Smart Cities, that they’re trying to
build in Africa.

71
