105
00:04:58,060 --> 00:05:00,910
And many African countries are authoritarian,

106
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:03,040
meaning they prefer China’s model

107
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:05,940
of a highly controlled internet.

108
00:05:05,940 --> 00:05:08,750
Chinese government officials have helped secure
internet deals

109
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:11,240
for Huawei throughout Africa,

110
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:14,480
starting as far back as 1998 in Kenya.

111
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:17,140
20 years later, Huawei has been responsible

112
00:05:17,140 --> 00:05:20,170
for connecting hundreds of millions of Africans.

113
00:05:20,170 --> 00:05:24,000
“It has built telecom networks in some 40
African nations

114
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:27,530
by offering inexpensive deals often financed
by loans

115
00:05:27,530 --> 00:05:29,610
with favorable terms and by providing

116
00:05:29,610 --> 00:05:31,660
on-the-ground customer service.”

117
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:36,510
Because of that, Huawei now dominates the
African internet market.

118
00:05:36,510 --> 00:05:38,920
And on one hand, that’s a good thing.

119
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:41,640
More people in Africa now have access to the
Internet,

120
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:43,040
especially through their mobile phones.

121
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:46,850
But the Chinese Communist Party had a long
term plan.

122
00:05:46,850 --> 00:05:49,670
According to the NGO Freedom House,

123
00:05:49,670 --> 00:05:52,910
most of Sub-Saharan Africa is not free.

124
00:05:52,910 --> 00:05:56,120
When those dictators realized the threat Internet
access

125
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,840
posed to their regimes,

126
00:05:57,840 --> 00:06:01,810
